{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, don’t rebuke me in your wrath, neither chasten me in your hot displeasure."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For your arrows have pierced me, your hand presses hard on me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "There is no soundness in my flesh because of your indignation, neither is there any health in my bones because of my sin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For my iniquities have gone over my head. As a heavy burden, they are too heavy for me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My wounds are loathsome and corruptbecause of my foolishness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am in pain and bowed down greatly. I go mourning all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For my waist is filled with burning. There is no soundness in my flesh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am faint and severely bruised. I have groaned by reason of the anguish of my heart."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Lord, all my desire is before you. My groaning is not hidden from you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My heart throbs. My strength fails me."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "As for the light of my eyes, it has also left me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My lovers and my friends st and aloof from my plague. My kinsmen st and far away."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They also who seek after my life lay snares. Those who seek my hurt speak mischievous things,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and meditate deceits all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But I, as a deaf man, don’t hear. I am as a mute man who doesn’t open his mouth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yes, I am as a man who doesn’t hear, in whose mouth are no reproofs."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I hope in you, Yahweh. You will answer, Lord my God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I said, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Don’t let them gloat over me, or exalt themselves over me when my foot slips.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I am ready to fall. My pain is continually before me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For I will declare my iniquity. I will be sorry for my sin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But my enemies are vigorous and many. Those who hate me without reason are numerous."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They who give evil for good are also adversaries to me, because I follow what is good."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Don’t forsake me, Yahweh. My God, don’t be far from me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Hurry to help me, Lord, my salvation."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}